Let's create a micro-blogging system called "snarksyndo".  It's architecture is going to
be: the contents is stored in github, each message is a short message which is committed
to the github repo, and then a github action posts new messages (that have not already
been posted) to Mastodon and Bluesky (then mark the messages as having been posted.  There
will be a companion app, which will get published to an associated github.io page, that
implements the client.  Necessary secrets, like the PAT for github repo access, and the
github repo location, will be stored in localstorage on the browser.  In short, the user
will go to a webpage on github.io, type in a message, and click a "post" button, and the
message will show up on their bluesky and mastodon accounts.  Please ask any clarifying
questions before beginng work.
